## Link to this sectionFAQ#

### Link to this sectionWhat file formats are supported for upload?#

Ultralytics Platform supports:

**Images:** JPEG, PNG, WebP, BMP, TIFF, HEIC, AVIF, JP2, DNG, MPO (max 50MB each)

**Videos:** MP4, WebM, MOV, AVI, MKV, M4V (max 1GB, frames extracted at 1 FPS, max 100 frames)

**Dataset files:** ZIP or TAR archives including `.tar.gz` and `.tgz` (max 10GB on Free, 20GB on Pro, 50GB on Enterprise) containing images with optional [YOLO-format labels](/datasets/detect#ultralytics-yolo-format), plus NDJSON exports

### Link to this sectionWhat is the maximum dataset size?#

Storage limits depend on your plan:

Plan| Storage Limit  
---|---  
Free| 100 GB  
Pro| 500 GB  
Enterprise| Unlimited  
  
Individual file limits: Images 50MB, Videos 1GB, datasets 10GB on Free / 20GB on Pro / 50GB on Enterprise

### Link to this sectionCan I use my Platform datasets for local training?#

Yes! Use the dataset URI format to train locally:
    
    
    export ULTRALYTICS_API_KEY="YOUR_API_KEY"
    yolo train model=yolo26n.pt data=ul://username/datasets/my-dataset epochs=100

Or export your dataset in [NDJSON format](/datasets/detect#ultralytics-ndjson-format) for fully offline training.

